<div id="review_2308291309" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2308291309" />
    <a title="M-" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/71808711-m-"><img alt="M-" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1570605613p2/71808711.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2308291309?book_show_action=true">Feb 25, 2018</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="M-" class="user" itemprop="url" name="M-" href="/user/show/71808711-m-">M-</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was ok"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was ok</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9781138821620" href="/book/show/22481283-feminism-is-for-everybody">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2308291309" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer11783779620681354117">I went as far as three quarters of this book and I just gave up. I am underwhelmed as it is the first Bell Hooks I&apos;ve read and I expected something quite different. Sure she covers many topics but I didn&apos;t feel this book is as accessible as intended. She uses concepts such as patriarchy, capitalism, white supremacy, etc. <u>a lot</u> and but she never explains what they mean. Pretty sure my mother or anybody who is not familiar with these concepts would be lost right from the beginning. A glossary shou</span>
  <span id="freeText11783779620681354117" style="display:none">I went as far as three quarters of this book and I just gave up. I am underwhelmed as it is the first Bell Hooks I've read and I expected something quite different. Sure she covers many topics but I didn't feel this book is as accessible as intended. She uses concepts such as patriarchy, capitalism, white supremacy, etc. <u>a lot</u> and but she never explains what they mean. Pretty sure my mother or anybody who is not familiar with these concepts would be lost right from the beginning. A glossary should have been included in this book.<br /><br />The first chapters are all about the ideological conflict between different trends of feminism (the reformist and the radical ones) and it is a very odd choice for an introduction to feminism. Then again she never explains what these labels actually mean. <br />Overall I was taken aback by her focusing so much on academics while deploring elitism in feminist movements. I was equally puzzled by her implying the feminist struggle took off in the 1960s when some women finally got teaching positions at universities and could therefore theorizing on feminist issues (in Europe, trade unionists back in the 19th century didn't write books but they advocated for girls' education, abortion, maternity leave and equal pay...). <br />I strongly disagree with some of her points (feminist masculinity ? meh, let's rather abolish gender) and the chapter about domestic violence made me angry. No, it is <u>not</u> a sexist stereotype to consider that men, as a group or a class, are more likely to abuse their partner and/or their children, although it is a sexist stereotype to consider that women, as a group or a class, are never prone to violence. There is something about social conditioning that should have been explained here (and backed with stats), and too damn bad if it challenges male readers.<br /><br />On a more positive note, I really enjoyed the chapters about race and decolonizing feminism so I will definitely read her book <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/250792.Ain_t_I_a_Woman_Black_Women_and_Feminism" title="Ain't I a Woman Black Women and Feminism by bell hooks" rel="nofollow noopener">Ain't I a Woman: Black Women and Feminism</a>.</span>
  <a data-text-id="11783779620681354117" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

